==English==

===Adjective===
'''syntopical'''

Coined by [[w:Mortimer Adler|Mortimer Adler]] in "[[w:How to Read a Book]]", referring to a type of analysis in which different works are compared and contrasted.
:''After finishing her syntopical of the presidents' speeches, she wrote an essay comparing the language used by Reagan, Carter, Gorbachev, and Qaddafi.''